 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search DevOps Security Engineer Genentech 960 reviews South San Francisco, CA 94080 Genentech 960 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description The Genentech Research and Early Development IT group seeks a talented and motivated DevOps Security Engineer to join us in implementing and supporting scientific software solutions. The job will utilize and build on your experience in software platform development, cloud computing and automation to continuously improve the security and compliance of a variety of existing and emerging technologies and applications. Your responsibilities will include working with a diverse team of scientists, software engineering staff and IT professionals to identify and design software and system security requirements. You will join a growing team of cloud computing and HPC engineers as well as laboratory IT support professionals with a variety of technical skills and experience in both technology and life sciences. Together you will have the 
 
opportunity to build a modern, secure research and development environment to help propel Genentech's drug development ambitions. 
The Genentech Research and Early Development organization is a world-class research and drug development organization. Staffed with some of the world's most brilliant scientists, bioinformaticians and computational researchers, the breadth and depth of scientific expertise across a broad range of disciplines can't be overstated. Encouraging an open, academic-like atmosphere and frequently publishing in top-tier, peer reviewed journals, scientists work with a variety of technologies including high performance computing (HPC), cloud platforms, modern software development tools, petabyte-scale storage, machine learning and artificial intelligence. 
Responsibilities 
Automate vulnerability scans and patching pipelines for operating systems and software 
Collaborate with engineers to develop frameworks for cloud and security operations 
Create threat modeling patterns developers can use to assess risks to their applications 
Partner with developers to identify and remediate software vulnerabilities and risks 
Assist Security Operations to ensure continuous compliance and security monitoring 
Continuously tune and configure security tools to reduce false positives and negatives 
Participate in Security Risk Assessments for compliance and process improvement 
Rigorously document and review the security of technical systems and processes 
Mentor team members and software engineering colleagues on good security practices 
Qualifications 
Minimum education level is a bachelor's degree, preferably in a technology discipline 
6+ years of experience in software development and cloud computing security required 
Ability to architect, develop, build and deploy software development tools and processes 
Demonstrated experience interpreting and acting on vulnerability findings (CVE, CVSS) 
Technical skills in operating system and container security using CI/CD methodologies 
Communicate effectively in both written and verbal form to non-technical audiences 
Excellent interpersonal skills with your own team, technical IT partners, and stakeholders 
